t=\dfrac{\sinh(\theta)}{1+\cosh(\theta)}
1-t^2=\dfrac{2}{1+\cosh(\theta)}
 \begin{align} \sinh(\theta)&=\dfrac{2t}{1-t^2}\\ \cosh(\theta)&=\dfrac{1+t^2}{1-t^2} \end{align} 
